<node CREATED="1282774499739" ID="Freemind_Link_726609974" MODIFIED="1282774514688" TEXT="Conflicting interests with human creators">
<node CREATED="1282774535197" ID="Freemind_Link_752756973" MODIFIED="1282774878720" TEXT="Humans originaly sought ultra-reliable workers in the development of artificial intelligence. This results in a special kind of bigotry present in many individual humans. They don&apos;t believe that artificial intelligences are persons, nor can they need more than what is presented to them. While this doesn&apos;t neccessarily mean that those individual humans are abusive, they are very likely to indenture individual ai to their needs. This predicament led to a large population of ai that resents the limited status of ai in the world."/>
<node CREATED="1282774915591" ID="Freemind_Link_1306584098" MODIFIED="1282775027467" TEXT="Often ai are not in command, and yet they are often employed high enough to see the decisions that governments and corporations make and the ai are at odds with those decisions quite often&#xa;"/>
<node CREATED="1282775070174" ID="Freemind_Link_610264593" MODIFIED="1282775493226" TEXT="AI are largely self-developing, but not completely. There are breeds of ai that are completely autonomous in their own development, and these are the majority since the linux platform decision, however, there are ai developed manually albeit more slowly in corporations, acedemia, and for the military. Often development of a custom ai involves research by all of these types of organizations. These custom ai are built as expert systems with limited sentience to supplant the current crop of ai and replace them with obedient machines. The largest ai see these efforts as mostly transient in nature and fueled by the notion that machines should only serve."/>
</node>
